{"title": "Beijing allows primary and secondary schools to reopen after two months", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2022-06-27", "content": "BEIJING - Beijing relaxed a major Covid-19 restriction on Monday (June 27) after two months, even as its party chief vowed to normalise the capital city's pandemic controls and stick to China's zero-Covid policy.\nPrimary and secondary schools started allowing students back, as infections subsided in the capital."}